{\fs20 \par After beginners have demonstrated that they can perform a skill with some degree of success, the emphasis of instruction should be on refining the skill and performing it more efficiently.\par }
{\fs20\expnd-1\expndtw-5 Instruction for closed and open skills should be similar for beginners, with an emphasis on their developing movement characteristics that enable them to experience some degree of \u173 ?
success at achieving the action goal of the skill. But after they have achieved this level of success, \u173 ?instruction for closed and open skills should differ. For closed skills the emphasis should be on the repetition of successful movements in situations that would occur in the environmental \u173 ?
context in which the skill would be performed; for open skills the emphasis should be on successful adaptation to a variety of regulatory conditions that would typify the open skill being learned.}
{\fs20\expnd-1\expndtw-4 \par }{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-2 Expect beginners to show large amounts of im}{\fs20\expnd0\expndtw-2\u173 ?\u173 ?}
